1
00:00:05,798 --> 00:00:09,050
ENTERPRISE<i> MEDICAL LOG,</i>
<i>STARDATE 5027.3.</i>

2
00:00:09,176 --> 00:00:10,511
<i>DR. LEONARD McCOY</i>
<i>RECORDING.</i>

3
00:00:10,636 --> 00:00:12,721
<i>I'M CONCERNED ABOUT</i>
<i>CAPTAIN KIRK.</i>

4
00:00:12,847 --> 00:00:15,182
<i>HE SHOWS INDICATIONS</i>
<i>OF INCREASING TENSION</i>

5
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,142
<i>AND EMOTIONAL STRESS.</i>

6
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,769
I HAVE COMPLETED
THE ASSIGNMENT, CAPTAIN.

7
00:00:18,894 --> 00:00:20,145
"A THEORETICAL INCURSION
INTO--"

8
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,397
YES, MR. CHEKOV.
I CAN READ.

9
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:25,442
AND AS USUAL, YOUR
THEORETICAL EVALUATIONS
DO NOT TALLY WITH MINE.

10
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,736
RETURN TO YOUR DUTY,
AND I'LL LET YOU KNOW

11
00:00:27,862 --> 00:00:29,697
WHEN YOUR WORK
IS SATISFACTORY.

12
00:00:29,822 --> 00:00:32,324
MR. SPOCK.
FULL SENSOR SCAN
OF THE REGION, PLEASE.

13
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:33,742
I DID GAVE A FULL REPORT
ON IT JUST--

14
00:00:33,868 --> 00:00:34,827
YES, MR. SPOCK.
THAT WAS THE PAST.

15
00:00:34,952 --> 00:00:36,328
I'M CONCERNED
WITH THE PRESENT.

16
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,413
OR IS IT BECOMING
TOO MUCH FOR THIS CREW

17
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:40,290
TO PRESENT ME
CURRENT INFORMATION?

18
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:42,584
NO, SIR. COMPLIANCE
PRESENTS NO PROBLEM.

19
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:44,294
THEN, MR. SPOCK, COMPLY.

20
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:47,965
SENSOR SCAN
TO ONE-HALF PARSEC.

21
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:49,174
NEGATIVE, CAPTAIN.

22
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:50,467
VERY WELL.

23
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,803
<i>I CAN FIND NO REASON</i>
<i>FOR THE CAPTAIN'S BEHAVIOR,</i>

24
00:00:52,928 --> 00:00:55,138
<i>EXCEPT POSSIBLY THAT WE'VE</i>
<i>BEEN ON PATROL TOO LONG</i>

25
00:00:55,263 --> 00:00:56,557
<i>WITHOUT RELIEF</i>
<i>AND DIVERSION.</i>

26
00:00:56,682 --> 00:00:58,934
<i>HE HAS RESISTED</i>
<i>ALL OF MY ATTEMPTS</i>

27
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,353
<i>TO RUN A PSYCHOLOGICAL</i>
<i>PROFILE ON HIM.</i>

28
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:03,731
MAINTAINING COURSE
AND SPEED, SIR.

29
00:01:03,856 --> 00:01:06,483
CHANGE COURSE.
COME ABOUT
TO 185, MARK 3.

30
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,945
BUT, SIR,
THAT'LL LEAD US

31
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:12,031
DIRECTLY INTO
THE ROMULAN NEUTRAL ZONE.

32
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:13,908
YES, VERY PERCEPTIVE,
MR. SULU.

33
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:16,159
I KNOW WHERE
THE COURSE CHANGE
TAKES US.

34
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:17,870
EXECUTE.

35
00:01:17,995 --> 00:01:20,205
AYE, SIR.

36
00:01:35,012 --> 00:01:38,223
INCREASING SENSOR SCAN
TO ONE PARSEC.

37
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:40,768
ALL SCANNERS REPORT CLEAR.

38
00:01:40,893 --> 00:01:42,269
NOTHING IN OUR
IMMEDIATE VICINITY.

39
00:01:42,394 --> 00:01:44,772
BETTER AND BETTER,
MR. SPOCK.

40
00:01:44,897 --> 00:01:46,231
CAPTAIN, LEAVING
NEUTRAL ZONE.

41
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:48,525
NOW ENTERING
ROMULAN SPACE.

42
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,360
VERY WELL, MR. SULU.

43
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:54,949
LIEUTENANT, WHEN DID
THE ORDER COME THROUGH?

44
00:01:55,074 --> 00:01:56,157
ORDER?

45
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:57,743
FROM STARFLEET.

46
00:01:57,868 --> 00:01:59,703
THE ORDER TO ENTER
THE NEUTRAL ZONE.

47
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:02,998
THERE'S BEEN NO ORDER
I KNOW OF, MR. SCOTT.

48
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,375
SURELY THE CAPTAIN
COULDN'T BE DOING THIS

49
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,543
ON HIS OWN AUTHORITY.

50
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:07,920
IF YOU TWO
HAVE COMPLAINTS,

51
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:10,338
YOU CAN BRING THEM
OUT INTO THE OPEN.

52
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:19,098
THAT'S A KLINGON SHIP!

53
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:24,561
BIT IT COULDN'T BE,
NOT IN THIS AREA.

54
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:28,356
INTELLIGENCE REPORTS
ROMULANS NOW USING
KLINGON DESIGN.

55
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:30,442
SOUND RED ALERT.
MAN BATTLE STATIONS.

56
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,319
STAND BY
MAIN PHASERS.

57
00:02:32,444 --> 00:02:34,738
BATTLE STATIONS.
ALL HANDS, BATTLE STATIONS.

58
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:37,074
[ALARM SOUNDS]

59
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:38,617
SECOND SHIP HAS APPEARED.

60
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,166
CORRECTION...

61
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:49,586
THERE ARE NOW 3.

62
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,591
WE ARE SURROUNDED.

63
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:13,318
<i>SPACE--</i>
<i>THE FINAL FRONTIER.</i>

64
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:22,703
<i>THESE ARE THE VOYAGES</i>
<i>OF THE STARSHIP</i> ENTERPRISE.

65
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:24,496
<i>ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION--</i>

66
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:27,290
<i>TO EXPLORE</i>
<i>STRANGE NEW WORLDS...</i>

67
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:31,670
<i>TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE</i>
<i>AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS...</i>

68
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:34,548
<i>TO BOLDLY GO WHERE</i>
<i>NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.</i>

69
00:04:16,048 --> 00:04:19,009
LIEUTENANT UHURA,
CODE A MESSAGE
TO STARFLEET COMMAND.

70
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:20,969
ADVISE THEM
OF OUR SITUATION.

71
00:04:21,095 --> 00:04:23,055
INCLUDE ALL LOG ENTRIES
TO THIS POINT.

72
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:25,390
MR. SPOCK, YOUR SENSORS
READ CLEAR.

73
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:26,558
WHAT HAPPENED?

74
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,060
I HAVE A THEORY,
CAPTAIN, THAT--

75
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,270
CAPTAIN KIRK,
I'M RECEIVING
CLASS 2 SIGNAL

76
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:31,772
FROM THE ROMULAN
VESSEL.

77
00:04:31,897 --> 00:04:33,648
PUT IT ON THE MAIN
VIEWING SCREEN, LIEUTENANT,

78
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:34,900
AND COMPLETE THAT MESSAGE
TO STARFLEET COMMAND.

79
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:36,568
AYE, SIR.

80
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,991
YOU HAVE BEEN IDENTIFIED
AS THE STARSHIP ENTERPRISE,

81
00:04:43,117 --> 00:04:44,576
CAPTAIN JAMES T. KIRK

82
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:46,286
LAST KNOWN
TO BE IN COMMAND.

83
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,205
YOUR INFORMATION
IS CORRECT.

84
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:49,664
THIS IS
CAPTAIN KIRK.

85
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,375
I AM SUBCOMMANDER TAL
OF THE ROMULAN FLEET.

86
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,335
YOUR SHIP IS
SURROUNDED, CAPTAIN.

87
00:04:54,461 --> 00:04:56,630
YOU WILL SURRENDER
IMMEDIATELY

88
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:58,840
OR WE WILL DESTROY YOU.

89
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:02,302
LIEUTENANT.

90
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,511
THEY WANT SOMETHING,

91
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:06,306
OR THEY WOULD HAVE
DESTROYED US BY NOW.

92
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:07,599
TRUE, CAPTAIN.

93
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:10,518
THAT WOULD BE
STANDARD ROMULAN PROCEDURE.

94
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:13,354
IT'S MY SHIP THEY WANT,
AND VERY BADLY.

95
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:16,191
IT WOULD BE
A GREAT PRIZE.

96
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:18,986
LIEUTENANT.

97
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:20,821
SAVE YOUR THREATS.

98
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:22,823
IF YOU
BOARD THIS SHIP,

99
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:24,741
I'LL BLOW IT UP.
YOU'LL GAIN NOTHING.

100
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:25,951
WHO IS THAT BESIDE YOU?

101
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:28,203
MY FIRST OFFICER,
COMMANDER SPOCK.

102
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:28,912
A VULCAN.

103
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:30,998
[BEEP BEEP]

104
00:05:34,126 --> 00:05:36,211
YES, COMMANDER?

105
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:39,256
YES, COMMANDER.

106
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:44,343
NO ONE SHOULD DECIDE QUICKLY
TO DIE, CAPTAIN.

107
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:46,972
WE GIVE YOU
ONE OF YOUR HOURS.

108
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:49,308
IF YOU DO NOT
SURRENDER YOUR SHIP

109
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,976
AT THE END OF THAT TIME,

110
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:52,686
YOUR DESTRUCTION
IS CERTAIN.

111
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,188
WE WILL BE OPEN
TO COMMUNICATION

112
00:05:54,313 --> 00:05:56,606
SHOULD YOU WISH IT.

113
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:59,567
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT
STARFLEET COMMAND

114
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:02,570
HAS BEEN ADVISED
OF THE SITUATION?

115
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,657
A SUBSPACE MESSAGE
WILL TAKE 3 WEEKS

116
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,534
TO REACH STARFLEET.

117
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,328
THE DECISION IS YOURS,
CAPTAIN.

118
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:10,620
ONE HOUR.

119
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:16,001
THE DESIGN OF THE SHIP
IS THE SAME.

120
00:06:16,126 --> 00:06:19,087
MR. SPOCK, YOU SAID
YOU HAD A THEORY

121
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:22,257
ON WHY YOUR SENSORS
DIDN'T PICK UP
THE NEW SHIPS

122
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:24,259
UNTIL THEY WERE
UPON US?

123
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:26,636
I BELIEVE THE ROMULANS
HAVE DEVELOPED
A CLOAKING DEVICE

124
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:28,763
WHICH RENDERS OUR
TRACKING SENSORS
USELESS.

125
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:32,267
IF SO, ROMULANS COULD ATTACK
IN FEDERATION TERRITORY

126
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:33,352
BEFORE WE KNEW
THEY WERE THERE...

127
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,687
BEFORE A VESSEL
OR A PLANET

128
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:38,023
COULD EVEN BEGIN TO
GET THEIR DEFENSES UP.

129
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:39,733
THEY CAUGHT US
RIGHT ENOUGH.

130
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:41,651
THAT'S A BRILLIANT
OBSERVATION, MR. SCOTT.

131
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:43,528
DO YOU HAVE
ANY HELPFUL OPINIONS?

132
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:45,030
WELL, WE'VE NOT GOT
MANY CHOICES.

133
00:06:45,155 --> 00:06:46,323
WE HAVE 3--

134
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,658
WE CAN FIGHT
AND BE DESTROYED,

135
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:52,620
OR WE CAN DESTROY
THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i> OURSELVES

136
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:53,997
AND KEEP HER FROM THE ROMULANS,

137
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,999
OR WE CAN...

138
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:58,585
SURRENDER.

139
00:06:58,710 --> 00:06:59,878
OPINIONS, GENTLEMEN.

140
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:02,005
IF THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
IS TAKEN BY ROMULANS,

141
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:06,343
THEY'LL KNOW EVERYTHING
THERE IS TO KNOW
ABOUT A STARSHIP.

142
00:07:08,387 --> 00:07:10,555
IF WE HAD NOT CROSSED
THE NEUTRAL ZONE,

143
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,140
ON YOUR ORDER,

144
00:07:12,266 --> 00:07:14,893
YOU WOULD NOT NOW
NEED OUR OPINIONS

145
00:07:15,018 --> 00:07:18,355
TO SUPPORT A DECISION
WHICH SHOULD NEVER
HAVE HAD TO BE MADE.

146
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:20,857
JIM, YOU ORDERED US?

147
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:21,983
YOU HAD NO AUTHORITY.

148
00:07:22,109 --> 00:07:23,277
DISMISSED, DOCTOR.

149
00:07:23,402 --> 00:07:26,696
JIM--
I SAID DISMISSED.

150
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:35,789
[INTERCOM WHISTLES]

151
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:38,125
BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN KIRK.

152
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,755
KIRK HERE.

153
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:47,050
THE ROMULAN VESSEL
IS SIGNALING AGAIN, SIR.

154
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:50,011
PUT THEM ON THE SCREEN.

155
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:52,222
AYE, AYE, SIR.

156
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:55,976
MY COMMANDER WISHES
TO SPEAK WITH YOU,

157
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:56,935
CAPTAIN KIRK.

158
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,519
PUT HIM ON.

159
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:00,521
THE COMMANDER WISHES
TO SEE YOU

160
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:03,817
AND YOUR FIRST OFFICER
ABOARD THIS VESSEL.

161
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:06,445
IT IS FELT THIS MATTER
REQUIRES DISCUSSION.

162
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:09,614
WHY SHOULD WE WALK
RIGHT INTO YOUR HANDS?

163
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:12,617
TWO OF MY OFFICERS WILL
BEAM ABOARD YOUR VESSEL

164
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,287
AS EXCHANGE HOSTAGES
WHILE YOU ARE HERE.

165
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:16,830
WHAT GUARANTEE
DO WE HAVE

166
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:20,917
THAT THEY'LL BEAM ABOARD
OUR SHIP ONCE WE'RE ON YOURS?

167
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,753
GRANTED WE DO NOT EASILY
TRUST EACH OTHER, CAPTAIN,

168
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:27,674
BUT YOU ARE THE ONES WHO
VIOLATED OUR TERRITORY.

169
00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:30,677
SHOULD IT NOT BE WE
WHO DISTRUST YOUR MOTIVES?

170
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:34,973
HOWEVER, WE AGREE
TO SIMULTANEOUS EXCHANGE.

171
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:40,937
GIVE US YOUR
TRANSPORTER COORDINATES.

172
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,647
WE'RE BEAMING ABOARD.

173
00:08:46,985 --> 00:08:48,903
ONE FINAL ORDER,
ENGINEER SCOTT--

174
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,489
IF WE DO NOT RETURN,

175
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:52,866
THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
MUST NOT BE TAKEN.

176
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:54,451
IF THE ROMULANS
ATTEMPT IT,

177
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:57,496
YOU'RE TO FIGHT,
AND IF NECESSARY,

178
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:58,997
DESTROY YOURSELVES.
IS THAT CLEAR?

179
00:08:59,122 --> 00:09:01,624
PERFECTLY CLEAR.

180
00:09:07,506 --> 00:09:08,548
ENERGIZE.

181
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,242
CAPTAIN KIRK.

182
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:38,495
COMMANDER...

183
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,539
I'M HONORED.

184
00:09:42,165 --> 00:09:44,251
I DON'T THINK SO...

185
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:47,587
BUT WE HAVE AN IMPORTANT
MATTER TO DISCUSS.

186
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:50,424
AND YOUR SUPERFICIAL
COURTESIES

187
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:53,301
ARE AN OVERTURE
TO THAT DISCUSSION.

188
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:57,305
YOU ARE THE FIRST OFFICER?

189
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:00,975
SPOCK.

190
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,104
I SPEAK FIRST
WITH THE CAPTAIN.

191
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:06,940
YOU MAY WAIT OUTSIDE.

192
00:10:10,444 --> 00:10:13,363
THE MATTER OF TRESPASS
INTO ROMULAN SPACE

193
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:14,739
IS ONE OF GALACTIC IMPORT,

194
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:17,658
A VIOLATION OF TREATIES.

195
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:20,620
NOW I ASK YOU SIMPLY,

196
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:22,205
WHAT IS
YOUR MISSION HERE?

197
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,498
INSTRUMENT FAILURE

198
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:24,832
CAUSED NAVIGATIONAL ERROR.

199
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:27,877
WE WERE ACROSS
THE NEUTRAL ZONE
BEFORE WE REALIZED IT,

200
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,254
THEN WE WERE SURROUNDED
BY YOUR SHIPS

201
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:29,921
BEFORE WE COULD
GET BACK.

202
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:32,132
A STARSHIP,

203
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:35,176
ONE OF THE STARFLEET'S
FINEST VESSELS?

204
00:10:35,302 --> 00:10:37,554
YOU'RE SAYING
INSTRUMENT FAILURE

205
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:40,432
AS RADICAL AS YOU SUGGEST
WENT UNNOTICED

206
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,850
UNTIL YOU WERE
WELL PAST THE NEUTRAL ZONE?

207
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:43,518
ACCIDENTS CAN HAPPEN.

208
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,479
CUT OFF, BACKUP
SYSTEMS CAN MALFUNCTION.

209
00:10:45,604 --> 00:10:46,813
WE WERE DUE FOR AN OVERHAUL
TWO MONTHS AGO.

210
00:10:46,938 --> 00:10:48,356
I SEE.

211
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:50,900
BUT YOU WERE ABLE TO NAVIGATE
WITH THIS MALFUNCTION?

212
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,693
THE ERROR WAS CORRECTED.

213
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:55,238
BUT I DOUBT IT IT WILL
CLEAR YOU OF ESPIONAGE.

214
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,782
WE WERE NOT SPYING,
COMMANDER.

215
00:10:57,907 --> 00:11:00,452
YOUR LANGUAGE HAS ALWAYS
BEEN MOST DIFFICULT
FOR ME, CAPTAIN.

216
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:02,621
PERHAPS YOU HAVE
ANOTHER WORD FOR IT.

217
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:05,915
YOU ARE GROSSLY MISTAKEN
IF YOU THINK THAT
WE WERE THERE TO--

218
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,961
CAPTAIN, IF A ROMULAN VESSEL
VENTURED FAR INTO
FEDERATION TERRITORY

219
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,963
WITHOUT GOOD EXPLANATION,

220
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:14,882
WHAT WOULD A STAR BASE
COMMANDER DO?

221
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:16,092
YOU SEE...

222
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:18,677
IT WORKS BOTH WAYS.

223
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,764
I HARDLY BELIEVE
YOU ARE THE INJURED PARTY.

224
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:27,312
SPOCK, COME IN.

225
00:11:37,197 --> 00:11:39,949
THE CAPTAIN HAS MADE
HIS STATEMENT.

226
00:11:42,118 --> 00:11:43,453
I UNDERSTAND.

227
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:48,375
I MUST ADMIT SOME SURPRISE
ON SEEING YOU, SPOCK.

228
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:51,586
WE WERE NOT AWARE
